HEADWORD: Citrange
<hw>Cit"range</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Citr</ets>us +
or<ets>ange</ets>.]</ety> <def>A citrous fruit produced by a cross
between the sweet orange and the trifoliate orange (<spn>Citrus
trifoliata</spn>). It is more acid and has a more pronounced aroma than
the orange; the tree is hardier. There are several varieties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Citrate</ent>⟦br⟧
